# shadcn/ui (exclusive UI layer)

**All user interface in this project must be built exclusively with [shadcn/ui](https://ui.shadcn.com/) components** from `components/ui/` (or the path configured in [components.json](mdc:components.json) after init).

## Non-negotiable

- **Do not create custom UI**: no bespoke styled wrappers, no one-off “component” files that duplicate shadcn patterns, no hand-rolled layouts marketed as reusable UI, and no substituting raw HTML elements for interactive or presentational UI where a shadcn primitive exists or can be added.
- **Do not use other UI libraries** (e.g. other design systems or component kits) for app UI.
- **Do not rely on ad-hoc HTML + CSS/Tailwind alone** for buttons, inputs, dialogs, cards, sheets, navigation chrome, or other standard UI—use the corresponding shadcn component (add it via the CLI if missing).
- If something is missing from the design system, **add the official shadcn component** with the CLI, then compose from those primitives only.

## Clerk authentication

- **Sign-in, sign-up, and any other Clerk-triggering controls must use the shadcn `Button` component** (from the project’s UI path), not native `<button>`, not Clerk’s default unstyled or pre-styled button components as the outer control, and not custom-styled elements. Wrap or compose Clerk’s elements (e.g. `SignInButton`, `SignUpButton`, `UserButton` triggers) so the visible, clickable control is shadcn `Button`.

## Setup

If shadcn is not initialized (no [components.json](mdc:components.json) at the project root, or the CLI says the project is not set up), run:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest init
```

## Adding components

If a needed primitive is missing, add it with the CLI using the name from the shadcn docs. Example for the Button component:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
```

Replace `button` with the desired component (e.g. `card`, `dialog`, `input`). Import only from the project’s configured UI path and compose pages from these pieces.
